UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, boys and girls in Thailand are increasingly protected from violence, neglect and exploitation

title.narrative: Policy makers and government officials in relevant Ministries have increased ability to legislate, plan and budget for child protection.

description.narrative: UNICEF continued to re-orient its focus on system-building to the policy level through discussions linked to the Mid Term Review coupled with other research around social service workforce and child protection system. Work to support law reform also continued, with completion of a study on Thai law's consistency with the CRC. UNICEF also helped organize and joined multiple sessions of the government's CRC@30 event, which includes over a dozen technical sessions organized for social workers and other experts from across the country. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
